WING (
Fig. 20A
). Micropterous, covered by grey microscopic setulae, no setae present.

TERMINALIA (
Fig. 5
). Right surstylus covered with long setulae, without microtrichia, bearing stronger setae mostly on dorsal margin, with several (ca 10) distinct denticles, ⅔ of which aggregated on distal apex. Right cerci with broad tip, left narrowing distally, both with long setae of unequal length on apical half, enclosed in epandrial lamellae. Left epandrial lamella ⅔ as long as left cercus. Left surstylus 2 times as long as wide, longer than cerci, with short setae of equal length on apical margin.

Similar to male, including being micropterous (
Fig. 20B
), except for following features: no distinctive hairs or setae on fore femur; spur on mid tibia absent; cercus pale brown with grey microtrichia and setae; no longer setae on apical sternites.
